Question: Many universities require that freshman live on campus dorm during the first year of college. In your opinion, is this a good or a bad thing? Explain your opinion on this issue.
Answer:
While living on campus certainly has some advantages, making it mandatory is not the right thing. The advantages of course are that one develops a bond with people fellow residents and also encourages one to participate  in extra curricular activities. But being usually very expensive, making it a requirement means bad news for people who cannot afford it.